Import Destinations

Instead of creating destinations manually, you can import them.

Context

If you have purchased a BUILD license, the destinations are automatically created when the administrator of your HCP account enables the BUILD service. If, however, you do need to import the destinations, download them from a server and save them to your computer before importing:
  • http://sap.github.io/BUILD_User_Assistance/Destinations/BUILD_Production
  • http://sap.github.io/BUILD_User_Assistance/Destinations/sapui5-private
  • http://sap.github.io/BUILD_User_Assistance/Destinations/sapui5-private-build
  • http://sap.github.io/BUILD_User_Assistance/Destinations/Web_IDE_PLUGIN
  • http://sap.github.io/BUILD_User_Assistance/Destinations/BUILD_Access

To import a destination:

Procedure

  1. In the HCP Cockpit select  Connectivity  Destinations .
  2. For each destination, on theDestinations page, select Import Destination.
  3. Navigate to the folder in which you have saved the destinations, then select the destination that you want to import.
  4. For the BUILD_Access destination, add the {providerAccountName} and the {consumerAccountName} in the URL field under Destination Configuration as follows:https://buildcockpit{providerAccountName}-{consumerAccountName}.hana.ondemand.com
    There are four provider account names, one for each SAP Data Center. You must enter the provider account name and URL that correspond to your SAP Data Center, along with your {consumerAccountName}. Note that the server is different for each URL. The URLs are:
    • Europe (EU1): https://buildcockpita7e7e7162-{consumerAccountName}.hana.ondemand.com/
    • Americas 1 (US1): https://buildcockpitb528657a6-{consumerAccountName}.us1.hana.ondemand.com
    • Americas 2 (US2): https://buildcockpitd5610ee76-{consumerAccountName}.us2.hana.ondemand.com
    • Asia-Pacific (AP1): https://buildcockpitc7ae52aad-{consumerAccountName}.ap1.hana.ondemand.com

    The consumer account name (number) is contained in the URL of the current HCP cockpit.

  5. Check the Connection.
